{"cursor":"10019","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\n'Representative democracy' is a variety of democracy founded on the principle of\nelected people representing a group of people, as opposed to direct\ndemocracy. All modern Western style democracies are various types of\nrepresentative democracies, for example the United Kingdom is a constitutional\nmonarchy and Poland is a parliamentary republic.\n\nIt is an element of both the parliamentary system or presidential system of\ngovernment and is typically used in a '[[lower chamber]]' such as the House of\nCommons (UK) or Bundestag (Germany), and is generally curtailed by\nconstitutional constraints such as an upper chamber. It has been described by\nsome political theorists as Polyarchy.\n","linknr":289,"url":"Representative_democracy","recorded":1362373378,"links":55,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Democracy","Elections"],"headings":["Powers of representatives","Representative democracy and republicanism","History","Criticisms","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Varieties_of_democracy","Direct_democracy","United_Kingdom","Constitutional_monarchy","Poland","Parliamentary_republic","Parliamentary_system","Presidential_system","Form_of_government","House_of_Commons","Bundestag","Polyarchy","Constitution","Constitutional_democracy","Constitutional_monarchy","Independent_judiciary","Constitutional_court","Supreme_court","Deliberative_democracy","Royal_Commission","Initiative","Referendum","Recall_election","Bicameralism","Upper_house","Canadian_Senate","British_House_of_Lords","Republic","Monarchy","Head_of_state","Islamic_Republic_of_I